<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATM FEE DISCLOSURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In "ATM Tuneup" (editorial, June 4), you state that the banks are reluctant to 
disclose ATM fees on the screen at the time of the transaction because bankers 
say it would "be inconvenient, though not technologically impossible" to do so. 
At virtually every ATM machine in Las Vegas, a message flashes informing the 
consumer of the transaction fees and asking him/her if he/she wishes to 
proceed.The ATMs are generally of the same manufacture as those found in 
California, and work on the same systems found in this state, such as STAR and 
EXPLORE. Once again, when dealing with those masters of integrity in 
three-piece suits, it's not a question of "can't," it's a question of "won't." 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN STEVEN SOET 
</P>
<P>
 Torrance 
</P>
</TEXT>
