<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; THIS ITEM IS RATED PG-13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Included in its comprehensive World Cup coverage, the Oakland Press of 
suburban Detroit offers a daily feature called "Kicks for Kids," intended to 
promote soccer awareness among youngsters. 
</P>
<P>
 One of Tuesday's tidbits for the kiddies: "Did you know . . . that a 1969 game 
between Honduras and El Salvador sparked a war that left 2,000 dead?" 
</P>
<P>
 Gee, Dad, where do we sign up? CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
