<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; ONE THUMB UP? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DOWNEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Recommending soccer-related videos now available for sale or rent, Donald 
Liebenson wrote for the Chicago Tribune: 
</P>
<P>
 "Despite the mania surrounding the World Cup, what soccer really needs to grip 
our imaginations is a good soccer movie. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 "Wim Wenders' 'The Goalie's Anxiety at the Penalty Kick' (1971), on Pacific 
Arts Video, chronicles the existential odyssey of a losing goalie, whose 
increasing alienation leads to senseless murder." 
</P>
<P>
 Yeah, love those soccer movies. MIKE DOWNEY 
</P>
