<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; HOME AWAY FROM HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irish goalkeeper Pat Bonner and his teammates couldn't stop talking about the 
reception they got in the New York-New Jersey area. 
</P>
<P>
 "We'd like to go back (for playoff games)," he said. "There were 50,000 Irish 
there (for the victory over Italy). If we can stay there, it would be great for 
us." 
</P>
<P>
 Giants Stadium, he said, was fantastic. 
</P>
<P>
 "The design was magnificent and it supported that kind of atmosphere. It was 
mostly Italians and Irish. It wasn't American people. I must say it was 
well-organized, So far, everything here has been a dream." HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
