WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; GEE, IT SEEMED EXCITING ENOUGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 World Cup '94 is the lowest-scoring tournament for 10 games. Only 23 goals 
were produced from Friday through Monday. The previous record was 25, set four 
years ago in Italy. ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
