<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; OH, DON'T WORRY: THIS IS ALL 
OURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While spectators at the Germany-Spain game in Chicago on Tuesday performed the 
wave, ESPN commentator Ian Darke informed his American audience that that 
particular form of fan participation was introduced during the 1986 World Cup 
tournament in Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
 His partner in the booth, former U.S. national player Peter Vermes, set him 
straight, telling him the wave originated with American football, well before 
1986. 
</P>
<P>
 "Well, I'd never seen it before then," Darke said. RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA062294-0038 </DOCNO>
