<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: THE ONE THAT GOT AWAY DOESN'T QUITE GET AWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 You wouldn't want to see the one that got away. It's rotting in the trash. 
</P>
<P>
 An angler at Green Valley Lake in the San Bernardino Mountains apparently had 
quite a struggle with an unusually large trout last Friday, but the fish 
managed to break the line. 
</P>
<P>
 It later surfaced -- belly up. Lake employee Jerry Eaker scooped it up, 
brought it in, weighed it in at 11 pounds, then disposed of it. 
</P>
<P>
 "We double-wrapped it and threw it in the dumpster," concession owner Jim 
Allison said. "It must have put up enough of a fight that it croaked." 
</P>
</TEXT>
