<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST, KUPCHAK ARE PROMOTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jerry West, formerly general manager, has been promoted to Laker executive 
vice president of basketball operations and Mitch Kupchak, former assistant 
general manager, has been promoted to general manager. 
</P>
<P>
 West, who had been the Lakers' general manager since 1982, will continue to be 
responsible for the club's basketball operations and will continue to handle 
trades, contract negotiations and scouting. 
</P>
<P>
 Kupchak, who had been contacted by other NBA teams seeking a general manager, 
signed a contract extension. 
</P>
</TEXT>
