<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; STABBING VICTIM, 18, REMAINS HOSPITALIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 18-year-old man remained hospitalized with multiple stab wounds Tuesday, 
after he and a companion were attacked the previous night by gang members in 
Sigler Park, police said.  
</P>
<P>
 The attackers mistakenly believed the two young men were members of another 
gang, said Westminster Police Officer Greg Jackson.He said the case is under 
investigation as an attempted murder. No one has been arrested. 
</P>
<P>
 Jackson said witnesses reported that the stabbing victim, Quintin Roman of 
Huntington Beach, was standing with Ricardo Cruz, 24, also of Huntington Beach, 
near a basketball court when several gang members accused them of being members 
of another gang. 
</P>
<P>
 After the two men denied belonging to a gang, Jackson said, witnesses saw 
their accusers leave the area. But about 15 minutes later when Roman and Cruz 
walked to their car, they were attacked by 10 to 12 gang members, he said, who 
stabbed Roman and beat Cruz repeatedly with a baseball bat. 
</P>
<P>
 Roman and Cruz were driven by a family member to Huntington Beach Medical 
Center, where personnel at about 10 p.m. reported the beating and stabbing to 
police. Cruz was treated and released, Jackson said, while Roman was 
transferred to the trauma unit at UCI Medical Center in Orange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
