<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE ARREST TEEN IN SHOOTING OF 2 GIRLS IN GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 16-year-old has been arrested on suspicion of attempted murder shortly after 
he allegedly fired more than 20 rounds into a passing car, wounding two 
passengers, police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the shooting occurred as the two victims, both teen-age girls, 
were leaving a party near Laramore Lane and Lewis Street just before midnight 
Monday. Authorities said the shooting was gang-related. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls were treated at Garden Grove Hospital and Medical Center. One girl 
was shot in the left leg and the other was wounded in the back. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they found two weapons, an assault rifle and a revolver, believed 
to have been used during the shooting. The teen likely will be tried as a 
juvenile, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
