<P>
SHIP CAPTAIN GIVEN 2 1/2 YEARS FOR SMUGGLING CHINESE IMMIGRANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The captain of a freighter that carried about 300 illegal Chinese immigrants 
to San Francisco last year was sentenced Monday to 2 1/2 years in federal 
prison. 
</P>
<P>
 Chun Teh Chong, 39, a native of Taiwan, has been in jail since May, 1993, when 
he and the crew of the Pai Sheng were overtaken at sea by Coast Guard vessels. 
</P>
<P>
 Chong, who was sentenced by U.S. District Judge Marilyn Hall Patel, is to be 
deported after his prison term. 
</P>
