<P>
 Yields Rise on Two-Year Treasury Notes: Yields on the notes rose in auction to 
their highest level in nearly three years.The high yield was 6.04%, up from 
5.94% at the last auction May 24. It was the highest rate since two-year notes 
sold for 6.14% on Sept. 30, 1991. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate 
of 6%, with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,992.60. A total of $17.01 
billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling $44.9 billion. 
