<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Art Institute of Southern California has added a fourth department, 
Continuing Education, to supplement its Fine and Liberal Arts and Visual 
Communications departments. The new department will be chaired effective July 1 
by Antoinette Geldun, who has been the school's director of 
photography.Specific continuing education programs have yet to be formulated, 
according to John W. Lottes, the institute president. 
</P>
<P>
 Canceled 
</P>
<P>
 The only Southern California date for the WOMAD world music festival, July 10 
at Irvine Meadows Amphitheatre, has been canceled. Primus, Arrested 
Development, Midnight Oil and Live were among the acts scheduled for the 
festival, which was also canceled for San Francisco, its only other West Coast 
venue. The festival is still scheduled on the East Coast, however, with founder 
Peter Gabriel to headline. 
</P>
