<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: COUNTY FAIR WILL OFFER COUNTRY, SOUL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tanya Tucker, the Marshall Tucker Band, two country groups and those old 
favorites the Temptations are among the entertainers scheduled to perform at 
this year's Ventura County Fair, which runs Aug. 17 to 28. 
</P>
<P>
 Country music singers Hal Ketchum and Carlene Carter will kick off 
festivities, the first of 17 performances at the 19-day event. 
</P>
<P>
 Ketchum debuted on the country music scene in 1991 with his album "Past the 
Point of Rescue" and this year released the album "Every Little Word." Carter, 
the daughter of country music star June Carter Cash and stepdaughter of Johnny 
Cash, earned a Grammy nomination in 1990 for her first solo country album, "I 
Fell in Love." She released her latest album, "Little Love Letters," in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 The Marshall Tucker Band, whose hits include the '70s tune "Can't You See," 
performs Aug. 19. On Aug. 22, the 1960s Motown group the Temptations, whose 
hits include "My Girl" and "Ain't Too Proud to Beg," take the stage. 
</P>
<P>
 On Aug. 23, All 4 One, a Southern California quartet that recently scored a 
hit with its a cappella remake of the 1963 song "So Much in Love," are on 
stage. And on Aug. 24, country star Tanya Tucker performs. Tucker's latest 
album is called "Soon" and includes the songs "We Don't Have to Do This" and "I 
Love You Anyway."  
</P>
<P>
 "Yesterday: A Tribute to the Beatles" is scheduled on Aug. 25. Starship 
performs on Aug. 27, and the Coasters close the fair with an Aug. 28 
performance. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
