<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: 5 ARE CHOSEN FOR AIR POLLUTION BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Representatives from five Ventura County cities were selected Tuesday to serve 
on a powerful countywide board that will shape air pollution policy. 
</P>
<P>
 The new Air Pollution Control Board members will be Oxnard Mayor Manuel Lopez, 
Thousand Oaks City Councilwoman Judy Lazar, Ventura City Councilwoman Rosa Lee 
Measures, Fillmore City Councilman Mike McMahan and Moorpark City Councilman 
Pat Hunter. 
</P>
<P>
 Ojai City Councilwoman Nina Shelley and Port Hueneme Mayor Orvene Carpenter 
will serve as alternates. 
</P>
<P>
 The board members were selected Tuesday at a meeting of the Assn. of Ventura 
County Cities, which includes elected officials from each of the county's 10 
cities. 
</P>
<P>
 Tuesday's action gives Ventura County cities a voice on the air pollution 
board for the first time. The city leaders will serve with the five county 
supervisors, who formerly made up the entire board. 
</P>
<P>
 The equal city and county representation is required by a state law approved 
last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County is classified by the U. S. Environmental Protection Agency as a 
region with a "severe" air quality problem, despite improvements in recent 
years. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA062294-0261 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 053786 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
