<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: TRAMMELL CROW NAMES CHIEF OF WYNDHAM ITS NEW PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trammell Crow Co. announced Tuesday that James D. Carreker has been appointed 
president and chief executive, effective Aug. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Carreker, 47, will remain president and chief executive of Wyndham Hotels & 
Resorts, a job he has held since 1988. He succeeds J. McDonald Williams, 53, 
who will become chairman of the Dallas-based commercial real estate firm. The 
company's current chairman, Trammell Crow, is retiring and will become chairman 
emeritus. 
</P>
<P>
 Carreker is credited with turning around the troubled Wyndham Hotels and with 
more than doubling the size of the Dallas-based chain, which is owned by the 
Trammell Crow family. The hotel company is not directly affiliated with the 
Crow real estate company. 
</P>
<P>
 During the past five years, Trammell Crow has shifted its focus from 
development to real estate services such as property management. 
</P>
<P>
 Carreker's "appointment speaks about where we see ourselves going in the 
service business," Williams said. "He has transformed Wyndham into a success 
story in a service-oriented business."  
</P>
<P>
 Trammell Crow, founded in 1948, is the country's largest commercial real 
estate service firm -- more than twice as big as its nearest competitor -- and 
manages more than 235 million square feet of assets. It also owns more than $8 
billion in commercial properties. 
</P>
<P>
 Hiroya Nobuhara has been appointed president and chief executive of Los 
Angeles-based Sanwa Bank California. Nobuhara, 53, succeeds Isao (Steve) 
Matsuura, who has been named general manager of the New York branch of Sanwa's 
parent organization, Sanwa Bank Ltd. of Japan. 
</P>
<P>
 This is Nobuhara's first U.S. assignment. He joined Sanwa Bank Ltd. in 1965 
and has held a number of management jobs in Japan and abroad since then. His 
most recent was as director and general manager of the corporate banking 
department in Tokyo, where he was responsible for managing the bank's largest 
commercial accounts.  
</P>
<P>
 Michael F. Henn has been named senior vice president and chief financial 
officer of Kaufman & Broad Home Corp., effective July 11. Henn, 46, was 
previously executive vice president and chief financial and administrative 
officer of Vons Cos. in Arcadia. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles-based Kaufman & Broad is a leading home builder in the West and is 
among the largest builders in metropolitan Paris. 
</P>
<P>
 GranCare Inc. has named Erich J. Wolters to the new position of senior vice 
president of operations, with responsibility for the operation of the Culver 
City-based firm's 80 facilities nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
 Previously, Wolters was senior vice president of Transitional Hospitals Corp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
