<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine broker -- The National Assn. of Securities Dealers has corrected 
information provided to The Times about Dennis Holtorf, compliance officer at 
Cruttenden & Co. in Irvine. The NASD now reports that charges of 
misrepresentation brought against Holtorf in a 1991 arbitration action were 
dismissed entirely and he was not required to pay a $1,000 fine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Correction 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
